The paper discusses a clustering ensemble approach that uses crowdsourcing to obtain multiple clustering solutions for image datasets. This involves collecting opinions from crowd workers, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of machine learning techniques such as Markov chains to achieve a consensus among the input clustering solutions falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The fact that the dataset being clustered consists of images suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the use of crowdsourcing to obtain multiple clustering solutions and achieve a consensus can be seen as a form of social computing (cs.SI).
